  China  may increase investments as
possible stimulus plans if the economy slows “sharply,”
 Michael Pettis , chief strategist at Guosen Securities Co., said
in an interview with Bloomberg Television today.  China’s debt levels are much worse than 2008, when the
government unveiled a 4 trillion-yuan stimulus package to
